(163, 29, 'cf_content_eng', '<p>Inspection on condition of cargo inside container is checking actual condition of cargo at postions can approach at the time of inspection. This items can apply for typical goods as follow:</p>\r\n<p>     - Frozen cargo</p>\r\n<p>     - General cargo packed in bag, package, bulk…</p>\r\n<p>     - Machinery.</p>\r\n<h4>Scope of inspection:</h4>\r\n<p>     - Inspection on lashing/securing condition of cargo inside container</p>\r\n<p>     - Check condition of cargo before exported/ after imported</p>\r\n<p>     - Check stowage, dunnage condition of cargo in container</p>\r\n<p>Benifits: to help applicant to know actual condition of cargo at the time of stuffing to container or un-stuffing out of container to have grounds for resolving dispute and protecting legal interest of the applicant.</p>\r\n<p>Our main customer: Maersk Line, OOCL, CMA, Amanda, Thai Binh…</p>'),
